ut I sure do love being able to see in the dark.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>Romidar Trueblade<BR>48th level Paladin<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">voards</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">i spent a long time looking for one of these on bertoxx, and never saw one for sale. a guild member of mine did get a ring a few weeks back, so they still are dropping off of the high shaman.<P>daryoon</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hivemind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yes, got one yesterday off the High Shaman in Sol A.  If they weren't lore there would be very lucrative trade to be had taking them to the Qeynos/Hallas area and selling them.  As it is it is probably too much trouble to drag them all the way over there.  I too have seen the shout go out that one is free for the looting on Xegony at least.  A group of low 30s or even high 20s and low 30s mixed should have no problem.  The key to Sol A seems to be not to rely on the girls blouse wearing tactic of invis in and invis out.   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif">  This will get you killed since so many mobs will see invis.  Do it the warriors way, fight in and fight out, at least if you get overwhelmed you know it on the way in, not in the depths with a full spawn behind you.<P>On a more pissed off note, I had to leave this room after being deliberately trained out by someone who wanted to powerlevel their friends in there and we were inconveniently in the way.  I am not one to throw about accusations like this freely and I am very aware that things can look like one thing but really be another, so I will admit that I am only 90% certain that this is what happened...twice.  I won't name names, but that person and their guild, have a very, very black mark in my book.<P>Hivemind (aka Grak, Troll Warrior)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Macgregor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">yeah, you should do as my guild does, we have a ****list on our website, making sure that no one on there gets any favors, groups, and we generally harrass the hell outta them     it's quite fun!<P><P>------------------<BR>Macgregor Bladestorm<BR>Steel Warrior of the 33rd Season **The Rathe**<BR>El'lar Dobluth</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">ALERO</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I have seen this auctioned twice on Prexus. Once for 40pp and once for 500pp. Both were sold on the same day. Needless to say I bought the 40pp one. My barbarian warrior has never seen more clearly.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Is there an item that gives ultravision?  Something that might be able to replace the guise?<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>45 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
